text: Saipal is a mountain in the Himalayas of north-west Humla district in Nepal. Api, Nampa and Saipal are a trio of high mountains located in northwestern Nepal. Together they form a small range of sharp, icy peaks, rising from a long, steep, snowy crest. ==See also== * List of Ultras of the Himalayas ==References== Category:Mountains of Nepal Category:Seven-thousanders of the Himalayas
title: Saipal
